    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-02T15:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-02T15:25:00-05:00" n="271"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4233: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-02T23:00:00+02:35"
                            >May 2, 1936—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 2—4:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>267. Fire is spreading but fortunately not in direction of Legation. Thousands of
                    natives have all day long been quietly evacuating the city. It would appear that
                    most of the damage was done by comparatively few rowdy elements who could easily
                    have been held in check by a small police force in the beginning.</p>
                <pb facs="0321" n="256" xml:id="pg_256"/>
                <p>It is almost inevitable that a report should be circulating that the Ethiopian
                    Government had decided to destroy the capital rather than turn it over to the
                    Italians but I do not credit it.</p>
                <p>Shall send no further bulletins until tomorrow morning unless the Legation should
                    be in danger.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
